        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                <pb facs="nei.n1a.10.54"/>
                <fw type="curatorial">54</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        April 29, 1971</dateline>
                        <address><addrLine>Dr. John G. Neihardt</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>University of Nebraska</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Lincoln, Nebraska</addrLine></address> 

                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Your appearance on the Dick Cavett television show, April 27th, was a thrilling experience for me. I loved every word you spoke &#8212; When you chuckled I chuckled.</p> 
                <p>I felt excitement when you said "Forward is the direction". Infact, I jotted down several of your sayings &#8212; I could not help but feel your great spiritual power.</p> 
                <p>You see, I have a lively interest in you, because in March I did a program on you for a few friends.</p> 
                <p>I am hoping that the story of your life will come out in book form. I want, so much, to have the privilege of owning and cherishing that book.</p> 
                
                <pb facs="nei.n1a.10.55"/>
                <fw type="curatorial">55</fw>

                
                <p>Mrs. Neihardt must have been an exceptionally talented artist. The great Rodin accepted only the potentially great. I keep wondering if she might have known Malvina Hoffman, who was also a student of the master.</p> 
                <p>Thank you for the many hours of reading pleasure that you have given to me.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely</salute>
                    <signed>(Mrs.) Grace C. Cook</signed> 
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>
                            206 E Marion</addrLine>
                            <addrLine>South Bend</addrLine>
                            <addrLine>Indiana 46601</addrLine>
                    </address> 
                </closer> 
                
            </div1>
            
